public void testCopyWithIndependence() throws Exception {
    XmlMapper xmlMapper = newMapper(); // annotations enabled by default
    XmlMapper xmlMapperCopy = xmlMapper.copy();
    xmlMapperCopy.disable(MapperFeature.USE_ANNOTATIONS);
    
    // Original mapper should still use annotations
    String xmlOriginal = xmlMapper.writeValueAsString(new Pojo282());
    // Copy should not use annotations
    String xmlCopy = xmlMapperCopy.writeValueAsString(new Pojo282());
    
    // Original must contain annotated name
    if (!xmlOriginal.contains("AnnotatedName")) {
        fail("Original mapper should use name 'AnnotatedName', xml = "+xmlOriginal);
    }
    // Copy must NOT contain annotated name
    if (!xmlCopy.contains("Pojo282") || xmlCopy.contains("AnnotatedName")) {
        fail("Copy mapper should NOT use name 'AnnotatedName' but 'Pojo282', xml = "+xmlCopy);
    }
}

This test is similar to the provided one but also checks that the original mapper is unaffected. In buggy code, if the cache is shared, disabling annotations on the copy might cause the cache to be recomputed without annotations, and then the original might also produce "Pojo282". That would fail the first check. So this test should fail on buggy code and pass on fixed code.

